Q: Given the following C code, predict the output:
```
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int a = 5, b = 10;
    if (a == 5) {
        if (b == 10) {
            printf("True\n");
        } else {
            printf("False\n");
        }
    } else {
        printf("Error\n");
    }
    return 0;
}
```

A: The output is "Error".

Q: Given the following C code, predict the output:
```
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int a = 5, b = 10;
    if (a == 5 || b == 10) {
        printf("True\n");
    } else {
        printf("Error\n");
    }
    return 0;
}
```

A: The output is "True".

